File: The Cricket SA head office. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Rob Walters and Shukri Conrad have been appointed as Proteas coaches. Conrad will lead the team in Test cricket while Walters mentors the ODI and T20 cricket. 56-year-old Conrad had reasonable success at the Franchise level, winning four trophies with the two teams. Conrad also had a stint with the Lions before taking up other local coaching opportunities. Walters' success was at the Titans were he won three trophies in three seasons before moving to New Zealand.